2026-01-01 00:42:02,931 - MetaFlow.llm.client - INFO - Execute tool write_file with args: {'content': 'import pygame\nfrom core.grid import Grid\nfrom core.economy import Economy\nfrom core.hud import HUD\nfrom core.buildings import Building\n\nclass Game:\n    def __init__(self):\n        """\n        Initializes the Game class.\n        Sets up the grid, economy, and HUD components.\n        """\n        self.grid = Grid()\n        self.economy = Economy()\n        self.hud = HUD()\n\n    def run(self) -> None:\n        """\n        Runs the game loop, coordinating all components.\n        Updates the grid, economy, and HUD in each frame.\n        Handles user input for building placement.\n        """\n        pygame.init()\n\n        # Screen setup\n        screen = pygame.display.set_mode((800, 600))\n        pygame.display.set_caption("Micro City Sim")\n\n        # Clock for controlling frame rate\n        clock = pygame.time.Clock()\n\n        # Load HUD assets\n        self.hud.load_assets()\n\n        running = True\n        while running:\n            for event in pygame.event.get():\n                if event.type == pygame.QUIT:\n                    running = False\n\n                # Handle mouse click for placing buildings\n                if event.type == pygame.MOUSEBUTTONDOWN and event.button == 1:  # Left click\n                    x, y = pygame.mouse.get_pos()\n                    grid_x, grid_y = x // 40, y // 40  # Assuming each grid cell is 40x40 pixels\n\n                    # Example: Attempt to place a House\n                    house = Building(x=grid_x, y=grid_y, type=\'House\')\n                    if self.grid.place_building(house):\n                        print(f"Placed a house at ({grid_x}, {grid_y})")\n                    else:\n                        print(f"Failed to place a house at ({grid_x}, {grid_y})")\n\n            # Update resources\n            self.economy.update_resources(self.grid.get_all_buildings())\n\n            # Update HUD\n            self.hud.update(self.economy.money, self.economy.energy)\n\n            # Render everything\n            screen.fill((0, 0, 0))  # Clear screen with black\n            self.grid.render(screen)  # Render the grid and buildings\n            self.hud.render(screen)  # Render the HUD\n\n            pygame.display.flip()\n            clock.tick(60)\n\n        pygame.quit()', 'path': 'core/game.py'}
