2026-01-01 00:43:05,743 - MetaFlow.llm.client - INFO - Execute tool write_file with args: {'path': 'core/game.py', 'content': 'import pygame\nfrom core.grid import Grid\nfrom core.economy import Economy\nfrom core.hud import HUD\nfrom core.buildings import Building\n\nclass Game:\n    """\n    The Game class manages the main game loop, coordinates the grid, economy, and HUD,\n    and handles user input for building placement.\n    """\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        # Initialize core components\n        self.grid = Grid()\n        self.economy = Economy()\n        self.hud = HUD()\n        self.running = True\n\n    def run(self) -> None:\n        """\n        Runs the game loop, updating the grid, economy, and HUD in each frame,\n        and handling user input for building placement.\n        """\n        pygame.init()\n        screen = pygame.display.set_mode((800, 600))\n        pygame.display.set_caption("Micro City Sim")\n        clock = pygame.time.Clock()\n\n        # Load HUD assets\n        self.hud.load_assets()\n\n        while self.running:\n            for event in pygame.event.get():\n                if event.type == pygame.QUIT:\n                    self.running = False\n\n                # Handle mouse click for building placement\n                if event.type == pygame.MOUSEBUTTONDOWN and event.button == 1:  # Left mouse button\n                    x, y = event.pos\n                    grid_x = x // 40  # Assuming each grid cell is 40x40 pixels\n                    grid_y = y // 40\n\n                    # Example: Placing a house on the grid\n                    house = Building(x=grid_x, y=grid_y, type="House")\n                    if self.grid.place_building(house):\n                        print(f"Placed a house at ({grid_x}, {grid_y})")\n\n            # Update economy based on the current grid state\n            self.economy.update_resources(self.grid.get_all_buildings())\n\n            # Update HUD with the latest resource values\n            self.hud.update(self.economy.money, self.economy.energy)\n\n            # Render the grid and HUD\n            screen.fill((0, 0, 0))  # Clear the screen with black color\n            self.grid.render(screen)\n            self.hud.render(screen)\n\n            pygame.display.flip()\n            clock.tick(60)  # Limit to 60 FPS\n\n        pygame.quit()'}
